<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880225-0019 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Savannah Electric andamp; Power Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SAV SO </CO><IN> TNM UTI </IN><TEXT>   Savannah Electric andamp; Power Co. said its shareholders agreed to the acquisition of the utility by Southern Co., Atlanta, in a transaction with an indicated value of $258.8 million.    Savannah Electric holders will receive 1.05 shares of Southern common for each of their 10.6 million shares outstanding. Savannah Electric, Savannah, Ga., will operate as an independent subsidiary of Southern, a utility holding company.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Savannah Electric was unchanged at $24.125 a share; Southern closed at $23.25 a share, down 37.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>